('63b2ea45ed6a01672669765', 'Stephan Schrock to retire from Philippine Azkals after AFF match vs Indonesia ', 8, '<p><img src=\"http://localhost/newswebsite/assets/newsassets/1672669571schrock-afp.webp\" style=\"width: 100%;\"></p><p><br></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">MANILA, Philippines–Stephan Schrock is set to play his final international match on Tuesday when the Philippine Azkals wrapped up their Asean Football Federation (AFF) Mitsubishi Electric Cup campaign against Indonesia at Rizal Memorial Stadium.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Schrock made the announcement during a pre-match press conference on the eve of the match that will serve as a non-bearing one for the Azkals&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://sports.inquirer.net/491660/philippines-azkals-wont-advance-to-aff-cup-semifinals\" style=\"border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">after missing out on a semifinals berth</span></a><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;after losing two of three in the group stage.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; background-color: var(--bs-body-bg); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\"><br></span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; background-color: var(--bs-body-bg); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); font-size: 19px;\">“As you know in football, nothing is for sure, but 99 percent, this would be my last game for the national team,” Schrock said.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; vertical-align: baseline;\"><br></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">The 36-year-old is expected to feature for his 57th cap for the Philippines spanning 11 years.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Schrock made his Azkals debut in 2011 against Sri Lanka in the first round of the Fifa World Cup Qualifiers.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">His first international goal came in the second round of the said qualifiers when he fired a strike late in the first half of the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://sports.inquirer.net/9345/azkals-fall-to-kuwait\" style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Azkals’ second leg match against Kuwait</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;before a big crowd at Rizal Memorial.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span></p><div class=\"ztoop\" style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><div id=\"anyclip_2021\" style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"></div></div><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">He also scored the Azkals’ only goal during the country’s maiden stint in the Asian Football Confederation (AFC) Asian Cup in the United Arab Emirates that came against Kyrgyzstan in the final group stage match.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Schrock also appeared in the 2019 and the pandemic-delayed 2021 Southeast Asian Games as an overage player.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span></p><div class=\"lfform-inquirer lfform-inquirer-horizontal form_inline related\" style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 100%;\"></div><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">But Schrock’s national team career also saw a dispute with former coach Thomas Dooley during the latter’s tenure between 2014 to 2018 and for a brief time in 2022 when the midfielder was left out of the Asian Cup Qualifiers squad.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">“It’s quite emotional for me,” he continued. “Not many know what I have to sacrifice, how many European contracts I jeopardized to come on for the national team [and] how many moments I missed out with my family so I sacrificed a lot.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">“There’s a time when you want to have it in your own hands. And given that I was selected in the AFC qualifiers, I think it’s a good time to step down and to enjoy the last 90 minutes of my Azkals career.”</span></p>', '63b2dcdc7acbe1672666332', '2023-01-02 14:29:25', '2023-01-02 22:29:58', 1, 0, 0, 'http://localhost/newswebsite/assets/newsassets/1672669957schrock-afp.jpg', ''),
('63bff7c62a9de1673525190', '2 PSU-UCC IT students earn medals at 11th IT Skills Olympics', 29, '<p style=\"line-height: 1.6;\"><img src=\"http://localhost/newswebsite/assets/newsassets/1673525050315644664_1154868878491870_9163788826035487233_n.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 18px; background-color: var(--bs-body-bg); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\"><br></span></p><p style=\"line-height: 1.6;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 18px; background-color: var(--bs-body-bg); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">﻿By | Vanessa Sido, News Editor</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px; background-color: var(--bs-body-bg); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">Two Pangasinan State University-Urdaneta City Campus (PSU-UCC) Information Technology (IT) students won two medals at the 11th IT Skills Olympics Competition with the theme: \"ICT at the Convergence of Education and Technology in the HyFlex World\" led by the College of Computing and Information Sciences of the University of Makati held at Makati City, Phillipines last November 11.</span><br></p><p><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Romar Macaraeg, a fourth-year IT student, and Dick Lomibao, the participant of C# Programming, won a gold medal and reigned as the Champion in the Web Design Competition and first place, which were coached by Leo Gabriel Villanueva and Rhenel Bernisca, respectively. Meanwhile, Jebson Ubaldo, a fourth-year participant of IT Quiz Bee, became a finalist.</span><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Among the students who also participated in the Olympics are:</span><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Joshua Yaacoub (Java Programming participant) Harmon Javier (Networking) Jan Maverick Agbunag (PC Disassembly and Assembly) July Rosal, John Brix Porras and Benjie Pecson (Application Development) Janus Abril, Junard Chua, Ronnie Cula, John Raphael Garcia, Miguel Laureta (E-sports)</span><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Each participant was coached by ICT faculty members Michael Acosta, Kathleen De Guzman (IT Quiz Bee), Brian Lapitan (Java Programming), Paul Andrew Roa (Networking), Ray Magat (PC Assembly/Disassembly) , Arnie-rie Tamayo (Android Application Development) and Joshua Reyes (E-sports) and was supervised by Dr. Frederick Patacsil, College of Computing Dean.</span><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">PSU-UCC extends appreciation to the students who participated in the said competition for proudly representing the campus.</span><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Congratulations to all the winners!</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Consultant | Aira Mae Delgado, Associate Editor</span><br style=\"animation-name: none !important; transition-property: none !important;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Creative Works | Jayson Nathaniel Tan, Editor-in-Chief</span></p>', '63a53731700701671771953', '2023-01-12 12:06:30', '2023-01-13 02:11:07', 1, 1, 0, 'http://localhost/newswebsite/assets/newsassets/1673525050315644664_1154868878491870_9163788826035487233_n.jpg', ''),
