('63c259bf383f01673681343', 'The Final Rendezvous: PSU President Buted\'s Visit to Urdaneta Campus', 29, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><img src=\"http://localhost/newswebsite/assets/newsassets/1673681304president.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\"></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">The entire 𝗣𝗦𝗨-𝗨𝗿𝗱𝗮𝗻𝗲𝘁𝗮\r\n𝗰𝗮𝗺𝗽𝘂𝘀 was abuzz with\r\nexcitement as everyone awaited the arrival of the incumbent PSU President, 𝗗𝗿.\r\n𝗗𝗲𝘅𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗥. 𝗕𝘂𝘁𝗲𝗱\r\nlast Thursday. The November heat did not deter the students and faculty from\r\nswarming the premises and the pathway toward the SAC building. By morning, the\r\ncampus was already decorated with balloons and posters, and most in-class\r\nmeetings were postponed to prioritize the momentous occasion.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">The President was greeted with joy and\r\nhospitality when he arrived in the late afternoon. Campus employees (both\r\nteaching and non-teaching) and students waved their festive balloons that represented\r\nthe university’s official colors, golden yellow, and royal blue. They seized\r\nthe opportunity to take pictures with him and welcome him to the campus. Upon\r\nentering the SAC building with the ROTC unit marching alongside him, a burst of\r\nconfetti filled the air, symbolizing how happy the PSUnians were for his visit.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">The program began with video presentations prepared by the colleges and departments of 𝗣𝗦𝗨 𝗨𝗿𝗱𝗮𝗻𝗲𝘁𝗮 𝗖𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗰𝗮𝗺𝗽𝘂𝘀. The 𝗖𝗮𝗺𝗽𝘂𝘀 𝗘𝘅𝗲𝗰𝘂𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝗗𝗶𝗿𝗲𝗰𝘁𝗼𝗿, 𝗗𝗿. 𝗛𝗼𝗻𝗼𝗿𝗶𝗼 𝗟. 𝗖𝗮𝘀𝗰𝗼𝗹𝗮𝗻, then delivered his welcome address and opening remarks. Afterward, PSU-UC’s achievements during the incumbent university president\'s tenure were presented. In the video presentation, Dr. Buted was thanked profusely for his valuable contributions.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px; background-color: var(--bs-body-bg); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">The program was followed by messages of\r\nappreciation from the various university directors and deans, as well as the\r\nstudent representative. Many of them recalled how Buted’s characteristics had\r\npositively affected their careers and improved the status of the university.\r\nThey praised him for his strong leadership skills and dedication to the\r\ninstitution which resulted in many noteworthy accomplishments that restored\r\nPSU’s glory. His attitude set him apart from the previous administrations -\r\nwhich is why many of them are sad to see him leave, but still wish him all the\r\nbest in his future career endeavors.</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span> <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">After a series of heartfelt messages, it was\r\nfollowed by a series of intermission numbers by PSU-Urdaneta’s faculty members\r\nand UPAG Students’ Dance Group. The President himself joined them during the\r\nlively performances. The crowd went ecstatic for Dr. Buted’s groovy moves on\r\nthe dance floor, creating an energetic and fun atmosphere.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span> <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">The moment everyone had been waiting for was\r\nnone other than Dr. Buted’s speech. He admitted, that while his administration\r\nwas not a perfect one, he acknowledged the milestones achieved throughout his\r\nterm. He mentioned how the administration invested plenty of resources,\r\nrecognizing that the PSUnians deserved to be prioritized to create a\r\nsignificant impact on the community. “The most important asset of an\r\norganization is its people,” Dr. Buted asserted.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Throughout his speech, the President\r\naddressed mainly the teachers and students of PSU. He emphasized the need for\r\nteachers to strengthen their core competencies. He also encouraged the teachers\r\nto be humble. Dr. Buted expressed, “As we grow older, humility should be placed\r\nin our hearts.” When the President pointed out that teachers should not fail\r\nstudents without first implementing interventions, many students cheered with\r\ndelight and approval.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\">Furthermore, Dr. Buted revealed that like\r\nmany other PSU students, he also came from a poor family who was not respected\r\nback then. He advised the learners to dream big, get out of the box, and listen\r\nto their teachers. <span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">His concern for the rising number of out-of-school youths\r\nprompted him to increase the number of student admissions, noting that the\r\nstudents are the bloodline of the institution.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"> </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Despite the many issues thrown against him,\r\nDr. Buted told the audience that he only responded to them with kindness. He\r\nrefused to retaliate or exact revenge upon those who instigated them. \"𝙔𝙤𝙪\r\n𝙘𝙖𝙣 𝙣𝙚𝙫𝙚𝙧 𝙜𝙤\r\n𝙬𝙧𝙤𝙣𝙜 𝙬𝙞𝙩𝙝\r\n𝙠𝙞𝙣𝙙𝙣𝙚𝙨𝙨,” he\r\nreminded. Dr. Buted was confident that the next president to take his place is\r\ngoing to be compassionate and capable as well.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"> </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">After his inspirational talk, the audience\r\nresponded with a salute clap for the President. Dr. Buted received a token of\r\nappreciation from PSU Urdaneta, which he accepted with warmth and gratitude. He\r\nwas also willing to be featured in a short and special interview by the\r\nTechnoscope Publications. Before he left the campus, dinner was prepared and\r\nserved for the president and guest speakers.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Dr. Buted is approaching the final lap of\r\nhis term and with his unforgettable service and triumphs, many will miss his\r\nleadership dearly. Fortunately, endings can lead to new beginnings and changes\r\nfor the better. As we move forward in unison, let us reflect on and honor 𝗣𝗿𝗲𝘀𝗶𝗱𝗲𝗻𝘁\r\n𝗕𝘂𝘁𝗲𝗱’𝘀 𝗹𝗲𝗴𝗮𝗰𝘆,\r\nand use it as a springboard to propel us further and attain progress.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Editor | Jessadine Rose JR Lucas Baluyot,\r\nFeature Editor</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Creative Works | Jeric Motea, Creative\r\nEditor</span><font color=\"#050505\" face=\"inherit, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 11.5pt;\"><o:p></o:p></span></font></span></p>\r\n                        ', '63c2568e1dd0c1673680526', '2023-01-14 07:29:03', '2023-01-14 15:29:03', 1, 0, 1, 'http://localhost/newswebsite/assets/newsassets/1673681304president.jpg', ''),
('63c25c3b5e0651673681979', 'ABEL\'s DAY: Forging Stronger Connections', 29, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span>﻿</span><img src=\"http://localhost/newswebsite/assets/newsassets/1673681936abelsdat.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">“𝑳𝒆𝒕 𝒕𝒉𝒊𝒔\r\n𝒅𝒂𝒚 𝒑𝒓𝒐𝒎𝒐𝒕𝒆\r\n𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝒔𝒑𝒊𝒓𝒊𝒕\r\n𝒐𝒇 𝒇𝒓𝒊𝒆𝒏𝒅𝒍𝒊𝒏𝒆𝒔𝒔,\r\n𝒄𝒂𝒎𝒂𝒓𝒂𝒅𝒆𝒓𝒊𝒆,\r\n𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝒂 𝒔𝒆𝒏𝒔𝒆\r\n𝒐𝒇 𝒃𝒆𝒍𝒐𝒏𝒈𝒊𝒏𝒈𝒏𝒆𝒔𝒔\r\n𝒇𝒐𝒓 𝒆𝒗𝒆𝒓𝒚𝒐𝒏𝒆”\r\n- Marvin Corpuz.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Through dedication and collection of efforts\r\nof the League of English Major Students (LEMS), a program dedicated to Bachelor\r\nof Arts in English Language, or ABEL students, commenced successfully last\r\nFriday, November 4, 2022, at the SAC building. ABEL’s Day became a joyous event\r\nand numerous activities that served as an avenue to meet their fellow ABEL\r\nstudents and forge stronger connections. ABEL’s Day program paved the way for\r\nall ABEL students of PSU-UC to come together and enjoy the fun-filled\r\nactivities prepared by LEMS. ABEL’s Day is for ABEL students. It served as\r\ntheir escape and a time to breathe from the challenges ABEL students face.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">“𝑰 𝒆𝒏𝒄𝒐𝒖𝒓𝒂𝒈𝒆\r\n𝒆𝒗𝒆𝒓𝒚𝒐𝒏𝒆 𝒕𝒐\r\n𝒎𝒂𝒌𝒆 𝒕𝒉𝒊𝒔 𝒆𝒗𝒆𝒏𝒕\r\n𝒎𝒆𝒎𝒐𝒓𝒂𝒃𝒍𝒆.\r\n𝑳𝒆𝒕 𝒕𝒉𝒊𝒔 𝑫𝒂𝒚\r\n𝒑𝒓𝒐𝒎𝒐𝒕𝒆 𝒕𝒉𝒆\r\n𝒔𝒑𝒊𝒓𝒊𝒕 𝒐𝒇 𝒇𝒓𝒊𝒆𝒏𝒅𝒍𝒊𝒏𝒆𝒔𝒔,\r\n𝒄𝒂𝒎𝒂𝒓𝒂𝒅𝒆𝒓𝒊𝒆,\r\n𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝒂 𝒔𝒆𝒏𝒔𝒆\r\n𝒐𝒇 𝒃𝒆𝒍𝒐𝒏𝒈𝒊𝒏𝒈𝒏𝒆𝒔𝒔\r\n𝒇𝒐𝒓 𝒆𝒗𝒆𝒓𝒚𝒐𝒏𝒆.\r\n𝑬𝒏𝒋𝒐𝒚 𝒕𝒂𝒚𝒐!”\r\nMr. Marvin Q. Corpuz, the Department Chair of the English Language Department,\r\nformally welcomed the students in his welcome address. He encouraged the ABEL\r\nstudents to enjoy the said program, participate in the activities prepared, and\r\nset aside the worries and stresses of today.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"> </span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">Further, Ms. Janilyn Grace Paleb, the\r\nadviser of LEMS, reminded that each of the students are competent enough to\r\nface their struggles. She then gave her motherly advice in her message;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"> <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">“𝑰 𝒌𝒏𝒐𝒘\r\n𝒕𝒉𝒂𝒕 𝒎𝒐𝒔𝒕 𝒐𝒇\r\n𝒚𝒐𝒖 𝒉𝒆𝒓𝒆 𝒂𝒓𝒆\r\n𝒇𝒊𝒈𝒉𝒕𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝒔𝒊𝒍𝒆𝒏𝒕\r\n𝒃𝒂𝒕𝒕𝒍𝒆𝒔. 𝑨 𝒃𝒊𝒕\r\n𝒐𝒇 𝒎𝒐𝒕𝒉𝒆𝒓𝒍𝒚\r\n𝒂𝒅𝒗𝒊𝒄𝒆, 𝑰 𝒘𝒂𝒏𝒕\r\n𝒚𝒐𝒖 𝒂𝒍𝒍 𝒕𝒐 𝒇𝒂𝒄𝒆\r\n𝒕𝒉𝒆𝒔𝒆 𝒄𝒉𝒂𝒍𝒍𝒆𝒏𝒈𝒆𝒔\r\n𝒘𝒊𝒕𝒉 𝒄𝒐𝒖𝒓𝒂𝒈𝒆\r\n𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝒂𝒍𝒘𝒂𝒚𝒔\r\n𝒓𝒆𝒎𝒊𝒏𝒅 𝒚𝒐𝒖𝒓𝒔𝒆𝒍𝒇\r\n𝒕𝒉𝒂𝒕 𝒚𝒐𝒖 𝒂𝒓𝒆\r\n𝒄𝒂𝒑𝒂𝒃𝒍𝒆 𝒐𝒇\r\n𝒂𝒏𝒚𝒕𝒉𝒊𝒏𝒈. 𝑻𝒉𝒊𝒔\r\n𝑫𝒂𝒚 𝒊𝒔 𝒇𝒐𝒓 𝒚𝒐𝒖.\r\n𝑬𝒏𝒋𝒐𝒚 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝒓𝒆𝒔𝒕\r\n𝒐𝒇 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝑫𝒂𝒚.”</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"> <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Afterward, the newly-elected League of\r\nEnglish Major Students (LEMS) took an oath for 2022–2023. Ms. Joanna Marie\r\nDelos Santos gave the organization the Certificate of Accreditation, which\r\ncertifies the League of English Major Students (LEMS) as an accredited\r\norganization in Pangasinan State University’s Urdaneta City Campus.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\"><br><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"\">Proving that ABEL students are indeed\r\ntalented, incalculable intermission numbers transpired as the students\r\nshowcased their talent and charisma.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"> <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\">An unfeigned message from Ms. Winky\r\nFelicitas, the Governor of the League of English Major Students voiced that after\r\na long time, they are blessed to see everyone’s lovely and vibrant faces as\r\nthey enlighten the torch of togetherness with a burning desire to promote the\r\nspirit of ABEL.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\">Cheers of the audience filled the building\r\nas the game took place. The students who initially said they didn’t want to\r\njoin the activities displayed their competitiveness as they went on with the\r\nfirst game as chosen participants. Each group, consisting of ABEL students from\r\ndifferent year levels, tried to connect to increase their collaboration and\r\nshowcase exemplary teamwork to complete each station swiftly and successfully.\r\nBecause of their chosen strategies, all the teams passed through all the\r\nstations. The blindfold Activity took place during the afternoon program.\r\nLaughter filled the building, which then again proved how the activities on the\r\nABEL Day entertained and helped the students quickly rest from all the\r\nchallenges every ABEL student had.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"> <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\">The crowd wearing their gorgeous outfits in\r\nneutral colors, the theme color for the event, enveloped The SAC Building. The\r\nevent won’t be complete without showcasing the ABEL students’ beauty, brain,\r\nand fashion: the most awaited Mini Pageant. The candidates walked elegantly and\r\ndemonstrated gorgeous poses and turns that stunned the crowd. From then on, the\r\ncandidates who captured the heart of the judges through their alluring charm\r\nand eloquent answers were Rochella Sequin, Michael Garcia, and Eiri Limon from\r\nthe 3rd gender category. The winning candidates received a sash and an award prepared\r\nby the LEMS officers.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\"> <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\">Ironically, mellow songs sung acoustically\r\nenlivened the students and hyped the crowd as they sang together with the\r\nmusic. The students gathered at the space and sang their hearts out while\r\ndancing with their friends and classmates. The afternoon breeze did not suck\r\ntheir energy out as the students formed a circle to “showdown” their dancing\r\nskills.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;inherit&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;Segoe UI Historic&quot;;color:#050505\">ABEL’s Day ended successfully with hopes of\r\ninspiring ideas and illuminating the torch of togetherness. The SAC Building is\r\nno longer just a building; it has become a threshold of the ABEL’s Day, as they\r\nwere finally able to ponder and create memories with their fellow ABELians\r\nafter two years of virtual classes.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n                        ', '63c2568e1dd0c1673680526', '2023-01-14 07:39:39', '2023-01-14 15:39:39', 1, 0, 1, 'http://localhost/newswebsite/assets/newsassets/1673681936abelsdat.jpg', ''),
