('63c2b9bb60db41673705915', 'OPINION | The Rightful National Hero; Bonifacion, not rizal', 29, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>﻿</span><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">﻿</span><img src=\"http://localhost/newswebsite/assets/newsassets/1673706312317644187_1165359527442805_2487502359219716840_n.jpg\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Cambria Math&quot;,serif;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Cambria Math&quot;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">By | Adnes Jay Estrada</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">As of writing, no law, executive order, or proclamation has been issued declaring any Filipino historical figure as the Country’s national hero. The&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝒊𝒍𝒖𝒔𝒕𝒓𝒂𝒅𝒐</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;from Calamba, Laguna, with his popular support, is undoubtedly the&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝒅𝒆</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝒇𝒂𝒄𝒕𝒐</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;national hero. Though, there are strong arguments against Rizal and in support of the&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝒌𝒂𝒕𝒊𝒑𝒖𝒏𝒆𝒓𝒐</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;from Tondo, Manila, for the&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝒅𝒆</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝒋𝒖𝒓𝒆</span><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;national hero.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">For the purposes of argument, the sole criterion for the basis of national heroism is purely the aspiration and struggle for the Nation’s freedom and independence against colonial powers.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">With this, Dr. Jose Rizal immediately fails.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Not only did Rizal not fight for independence, but our beloved martyr fought for the Philippines to be a province of Spain.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Yes. You read that right.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Rizal, alongside Marcelo H. Del Pilar, Graciano Lopez Jaena, and other propagandists published</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝑳𝒂</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝑺𝒐𝒍𝒂𝒓𝒊𝒅𝒂𝒅</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;which advocated the integration of the Philippines as a province of Spain and its representation in the&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝑪𝒐𝒓𝒕𝒆𝒔</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;(Spanish Parliament).</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">As to the means to the end of independence, as written in his manifesto, Rizal fought for intellectual reformism, also contradictory to the rebels’ revolutionary reforms:</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Rizal was, without a shadow of doubt, a genius. For not only was he a polymath and polyglot, but could also forecast the future. If independence were to come, Rizal feared that the Philippines could not stand her own when faced by other imperialistic empires like England, Germany, and Japan, which would mirror the then status-quo in every possible way but name. In fact, in The Philippines a Century Hence, Rizal prophesized that the United States could also be one of these imperialistic nations, which, they were.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">In El Fili, through the personification of silent wisdom and secular pragmatism – Father Florentino, Rizal stressed his disapproval of hasty independence by writing:</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">The pacifist Rizal was maliciously chosen by American colonizers to stand as a “good example” for Juan Dela Cruz by unilaterally deciding a writer, not a warrior, was the Nation’s Hero.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-size: 19px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Bonifacio’s legacy of designing a bloody revolution against colonizers posed a threat to the American imperialists. Though their bald eagle symbolizes freedom and their statues are named after liberty, both were loathed for Filipinos.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Like in many of Nature’s designs, we find ourselves trapped in a dichotomy – man and woman, dark and light, yin and yang, reformist and revolutionary, intellectual and rebel, elite and simple, pen and sword,&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝐑𝐢𝐳𝐚𝐥</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝐚𝐧𝐝</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝐁𝐨𝐧𝐢𝐟𝐚𝐜𝐢𝐨</span><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Without Bonifacio, our sense of Nationhood wouldn’t have come into existence and we would have no “National Hero” to argue about. Rizal aspired for the&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝒊𝒏𝒅𝒊𝒐𝒔</span><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;to become Spaniards; Bonifacio fought to create what we now call The Filipino.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">This, alone, makes&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝑻𝒉𝒆</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">𝑺𝒖𝒑𝒓𝒆𝒎𝒐</span><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">&nbsp;reign supreme over all other Filipino heroes.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Consultant | Mr. Emil Isaac Conde, Adviser</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Cartoon | Benson Mata, Editorial Cartoonist</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">Layout | Jayson Nathaniel Tan, Editor-in-Chief</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/thetechnoscopepublications?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__%5b0%5d=AZV8NzKvmKzeb3AWIdbvcH7giiNmkDbl-SXH-oHZkOnaydjXLvBuE0KU98USc1tjFPr7pkpJF85bfFV9Lv-21GEPPxuDTyKvtAqzfVNIyu_LYyNtcU_wsqSonD_ZHH_7FJBXNWNlE6zg_soZUrenGT2CB0jKLstcstgT0hxMkRsyGQ5woJlk7I5cbwqUtpc7u74&amp;__tn__=*NK-R\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\">#TheTechnoscopePublications</span></a><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 19px;\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/bonifacioday?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__%5b0%5d=AZV8NzKvmKzeb3AWIdbvcH7giiNmkDbl-SXH-oHZkOnaydjXLvBuE0KU98USc1tjFPr7pkpJF85bfFV9Lv-21GEPPxuDTyKvtAqzfVNIyu_LYyNtcU_wsqSonD_ZHH_7FJBXNWNlE6zg_soZUrenGT2CB0jKLstcstgT0hxMkRsyGQ5woJlk7I5cbwqUtpc7u74&amp;__tn__=*NK-R\">#BonifacioDay</a></span></p>', '63c2b8320e8941673705522', '2023-01-14 14:18:35', '2023-01-14 22:20:36', 1, 0, 0, 'http://localhost/newswebsite/assets/newsassets/1673706312317644187_1165359527442805_2487502359219716840_n.jpg', '');
